column5: thanks they were bigger then Lloyds lakers, but I wasn't going to say anything...LOL  It was a pretty good day I caught a bigger one with a real hump back, but it went back down the hole without posing for a photo
I would have never believed that Wayne's pin was bigger than your hole Terry! My how times have changed! Nice pics guys! HH
LOL  but it was the other way around
Oops... sorry about that, but in reality, that makes it even harder to believe! LOL HH
Freaky when you are travelling with little visablilty on the ice.  Great job again, you've definitely are dailed in on Simcoe Terry.
Nicely done boys...I GOTTA get out there with you...one of these times....looks like season is winding down...sheesh!
Well Done Lads!  Congrats Terry and Crew  NICE Chunky WF on the right there!  Cheers  Paul  BELIEVE
you need to get a sled and you can come anytime. ill be out sat and sunday
thanks guys  Lloyd I will be out at lest one day on the weekend
Is it gonna be bare ice out there....?? /?/??
if we get sunny days for the rest of the week...yup
I don't have scratchers...
it's time you get them.......lol royal dis. has them
Don't have time for that trip.. guess I'll have to make some !!
i hope to see you guys out there saturday or sunday
I'm hoping to get enough done this week that I can take Saturday off Jose...
I'm hopping myself to have time to do some fishing with you old guys
there is still lots of snow on simcoe right now

got out on simcoe today,  80ft of water and started marking fish right away but I couldn't get them to the hole, lost 5 fish... then I was off to find Lloyd tom get my spare tire back, it was one heck of a trip couldn't see 25 ft in front of the sled, flew over some pressure cracks that I saw too later to stop but saw the big one and stopped, the I got stuck in the  slush I had to  disconnect the hut to get out of it, then off I go it was snowng so hard my GPS lost the satellites...I was lost....a phone call to Lloyd and I was on the road(so to speak0 again  as soon as I got there the lake trout stopped biting, the skies cleared a bit so I took off back to IBP.... 77 ft of water drilled a couple of holes and started catching whities, I wasn't going to take any home but 2 were hurt so they are diner I called    Fishhunter and Aile Goby and they came to were I was catching all them whitefish but shortly after they arrived the bite stopped, I had my limit kept so I took off home , so I don't know how they made out, but it was a great day playing on simcoe..        oh yeah my fishfinder got moisture in it again and died  only a couple of weekends left to get them on simcoe..(a tear comes to my eye)
Looks like a fun day Terry..
Buggers!!!  Shove the HS5 back up Lowrances
you bet fishfinders get wet when fishing, I am sure they will fix me  maybe they  will throw in a structure scan unit to make me feel better  LOL

I'm sorry Wayne lol I even let you sleep in lmao get some work done so you can come out and play next weekend. the weekend after that i took off a few days to fish simcoe fri sat sun then she is closed

Terry I hit one on the way home that put me about 3 feet in the air lol  what a rush lol We marked 2 fish after you left then moved 6 miles and marked 2 fish then went home. It was a great day all in all and showed my partner how to play with the lakers and get them hit.
Well I'm glad to see you finally got into them on Simcoe Terry, way to go bud  Joey
Now one day i will get me a damn laker lol Same goes for them whites.  Had fun as and can't wait till next week when i should have new new hut.
good to see you guys out there, sorry the bite stopped  I am  kind of   thinking about going out for the morning bite tomorrow, those whites seems they are early risers
Yah.. sorry my    !!  But I accomplished something today at least...
.get her done.  Wayne, where did you get the pin that you lent me to hold my hut on the skidoo and what do you all that, I need to get one  or two
looks like a nice catch! i like the auger set up too!

I actually meant to leave it with you.. but stole it to go get the mega hut from Doug.  Princess Auto... PTO pin. That one was 5/16 diameter I believe.. Check what your hitch hole is and shop accordingly. They're only $5 or so.

yeah yours was a little loose in my hole.............what did I just say.....dang...lets try again  the pin you lent me was too skinny for the towbar hole..that sounds better...but it worked well thanks I will check it out
Like throwing a hot dog down a hallway...
lOL
great day on the water congrats
Nice work there Terry, Sure did get mild out there today and packed that snow down pretty good by the end of the day.   Rob C

Great report and pics Terry Man talk about adventures..... first you lost the hair on your fingers at Temagami and then getting stuck into slush on Simcoe    Never a boring moment on your outings  You got into some nice ones.... good going!!! Thanks for sharing Leechman
thanks  it's all part of the adventure, if you come back in one piece,,,,,,it was a good day...LOL
Oh, I see. You wanted to get fish on Simcoe. So we where left out.(we as in I  )
I do have trouble getting whitie when you guys are there  next saturday we could try again
Well i cant tell a lie, I was not near you when you got your fish terry lol but ill be out next sat right beside you lol
well if nothing else you got to watch lakers in action and even got to sting 4 of them. It was fun teaching you today and maybe next weekend we can get you to land one lol
those whities are huge man!  congrats!
